"title": "2075: Jesus Christ, sinlessness of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2075",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The complete absence of sin, only in Jesus Christ. Christ demonstrated complete obedience to God in spite of his human frailty, enabling him to be a perfect atoning sacrifice and to give his righteousness to sinners.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ fully experienced human weakness</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7\">PHP 2:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ was tempted to sin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:2-Matt4:3\">MAT 4:2–4:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:2-Luke4:3\">LUK 4:2–4:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:12-Mark1:13\">MRK 1:12–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:32\">MRK 8:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:22\">MAT 16:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:29-Mark15:30\">MRK 15:29–15:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:40\">MAT 27:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:37\">LUK 23:37</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ resisted the temptation to sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:4\">LUK 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">MAT 16:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:33\">MRK 8:33</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ committed no sin</h2>\n<h3>He only spoke the truth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:9\">ISA 53:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:7\">ISA 53:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:46\">JHN 8:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:46\">JHN 8:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></p>\n<h3>He fulfilled the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17\">MAT 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:15\">MAT 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:27\">LUK 24:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:44\">LUK 24:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:4\">ROM 10:4</a></p>\n<h3>He was fully obedient to his human parents</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:51\">LUK 2:51</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:26\">JHN 19:26</a></p>\n<h3>He was fully obedient to his heavenly Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:4\">JHN 17:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:19\">JHN 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:36\">JHN 5:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:49\">JHN 8:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:49-John12:50\">JHN 12:49–12:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7-Heb5:8\">HEB 5:7–5:8</a></p>\n<h3>He was innocent according to Roman law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:14-Luke23:15\">LUK 23:14–23:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:21\">MAT 22:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:17\">MRK 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:25\">LUK 20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:19\">MAT 27:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:4\">LUK 23:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:22\">LUK 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:28\">ACT 13:28</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's sinlessness was recognised by others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:47\">LUK 23:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:41\">LUK 23:41</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ was perfect</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:28\">HEB 7:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19\">COL 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:10\">HEB 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:9\">HEB 5:9</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's sinlessness qualified him to be the perfect sacrifice</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a></strong> <em>NIV footnote.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's sinlessness is the grounds of believers' sanctification</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:14\">HEB 10:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:11\">ISA 53:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:19\">ROM 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:4\">ROM 8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a></p>",
